# Environment Variables Configuration

## WebSocket Configuration

Add the following to your `.env.local` file in the frontend directory:

```bash
# Development (Backend running on localhost:8000)
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_HOST=ws://localhost:8000

# Production (Replace with your actual domain)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_HOST=wss://your-domain.com
```

## Notes

- The `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix makes the variable available in the browser
- Use `ws://` for development (HTTP)
- Use `wss://` for production (HTTPS)
- The WebSocket connects to: `{NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_HOST}/ws/notifications/?token={jwt_token}`

## Setting Up

```bash
cd frontend
echo "NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_HOST=ws://localhost:8000" >> .env.local
```

After adding the variable, restart your development server:

```bash
npm run dev
```
